<item>
            <title>[BATCH-926] vague skip limit for concurrent chunks</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-926</link>
                <project id="10090" key="BATCH">Spring Batch</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When chunks execute concurrently each chunk works with its own local copy of skipCount (from StepContribution). Given skipLimit=1 and 10 chunks execute concurrenlty we can end up with successful job execution and 10 skips. As the number of concurrent chunks increases the skipLimit becomes more a limit per chunk rather than job.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
